pull.title: [qa] python-bitcoinrpc is no longer a subtree
pull.body:
Follow up of #6097?

Not sure what we are doing right now, but it is no longer a subtree.

[ci skip]

events.body: I'm happy to sync up, however, as @jonasschnelli says, only some of the files are from python-bitcoinrpc.

events.message:
[qa] python-bitcoinrpc is no longer a subtree

* Only authproxy.py is taken from the python-bitcoinrpc

events.body:
ACK

On Thursday, November 19, 2015, Jonas Schnelli notifications@github.com
wrote:

> ACK
> 
> â€”
> Reply to this email directly or view it on GitHub
> https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/pull/7052#issuecomment-158044816.

Right. What we use amounts to only one file (`authproxy.py`), and it is a very stable library, so it is easier to just copy it and make it part of the test framework than keep around a subtree. The subtree needed a circuitous work-around (updating sys.path) to use it in place.
